  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Electrical)",
  "description": "<h2>Job Description &amp; Requirements</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare proposal and budget estimates for new contracts / tenders.</li>\n  <li>Develop, review and monitor the compliance of the tender and contracts policies and guidelines, in line with the industry's best practice.</li>\n  <li>Liaise and negotiate with clients, vendors, contractors, sub-contractors and consultants on project requirement.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with tender team in preparation of tender submission.</li>\n  <li>A great eyes for details in evaluating quotation, assess variation order (VO), escalation, abortive work, measure quantities / taking off and accounts finalization.</li>\n  <li>Scope of Work:<br>\n1. Estimation &amp; Quantity Taking-Off<br>\n2. Request for Quotation and Prepare Detail Comparison<br>\n3. Cost Preparation &amp; Rate Rationalize<br>\n4. Prepare Tender Documentation<br>\n5. Update Cost Data Library<br>\n6. Contract Administration<br>\n7. Progress Claim Preparation<br>\n8. Variation Order Preparation<br>\n9. Final Account</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Job Requirements :</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum Diploma in Electrical Engineering.</li>\n  <li>Strong interpersonal skills with prior cost estimation experience in a M&amp;E construction environment.</li>\n  <li>Demonstrated problem-solving skills with the ability to critically analyze issues and creatively identify solutions.</li>\n  <li>High level of initiative, independent and meticulous.</li>\n  <li>Able to work under tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of working experience in the related field.</li>\n  <li>Well versed in Ms Excel, AutoCAD.</li>\n  <li>Preferably able to use BIM software like Revit/ Cubicost.</li>\n  <li>Willingness to work at Tuas area with transportation pickup at designated MRT station.</li>\n</ul>",
